cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SY, cs.GR 

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics): The paper proposes a computational design tool for quadrotor trajectories, which falls under the domain of robotics. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The algorithm proposed in the paper is optimization-based and incorporates high-level human objectives, which suggests the use of AI techniques. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision): One of the real-world application scenarios mentioned in the paper is aerial-videography, which involves capturing images or videos from the quadrotor. This could involve the use of computer vision techniques for object detection or tracking. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper mentions the generation of feasible trajectories that can be flown in the real world, which involves control of the quadrotor system. 
- cs.GR (Graphics): The paper mentions an easy-to-use 3D design tool for trajectory specification and editing, which suggests the use of graphics techniques.
